 The Kenya Revenue Authority will today host the fourth Annual Tax Summit at The Kenya School of Monetary Studies, Nairobi. ALSO READ:

Tax evasion costs Kenya Sh90b The three-day event will bring together local and global experts to deliberate on emerging taxation practices. National Treasury CS Henry Rotich said the event was meant to debate tax challenges at strategic and operational levels. He urged the public to use the opportunity to root for evidence-based tax policy formulation and implementation.